HEADWORD: Korinthos
<hw>Korinthos</hw> <pos>prop. prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Greek.]</ety> <def>A
city in Greece, called <altname>Corinth</altname> in English; the modern
city is near the site of the ancient city that was 2nd only to Athens in
size and power in ancient Greece.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Corinth.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

